author: @Jake3D
text: For windows to access TensorBoard on windows tensorboard --logdir=foo:"Dir\log" where Dir is the location where you save your code. (Edit) the doulbe = isnt nessary. Note the double quotes around the directory because where I save my files there are spaces. If you save in a dir like C:\Python_TUT_Files then you don't need the quotes. However if you save "C:\Users\User\Documents\Python Files\Tutorial Files\..." you do need the quotes because of the space and don't forget to add \log at the end. Once you have executed this in command prompt you can use the IP address listed or use http://localhost:6006 both should work. If it says "No dashboards are active for the current data set." then the directory you entered is wrong in some way. Try and recopy the DIR and put it in quotes.  If this still isn't working for you you could try double = before the foo. It seemed like it was necessary for me but I was able to get it working without it as well.  Hope this Helps
